# Vercel bundles everything not excluded here into the Python function
# zip. backend/.venv is ~133MB on its own, which pushes the function
# over Vercel's 250MB unzipped size limit. Exclude it and other local
# dev / test artifacts that don't need to run in the serverless function.
#
# IMPORTANT: do not exclude `frontend/src/` or `frontend/node_modules/`
# — those are needed during the Vite build step (buildCommand runs
# `cd frontend && npm install && npm run build`).

# Python virtualenv (local dev only, never runs on Vercel)
backend/.venv/

# Test files (not needed at runtime)
backend/tests/

# Python bytecode caches
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo

# Git + docs noise that doesn't need to be in the function bundle
.git/
docs/
*.md

# Repo-root supabase/ (migrations, seed.sql) — NOT the pip-installed
# supabase Python package. We exclude here at clone-time instead of
# via vercel.json's excludeFiles glob because that glob also matched
# the nested `python_packages/supabase/` path, breaking the runtime
# import: `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'supabase'`.
supabase/
